==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kilderkin
<hw>Kil"der*kin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OD.
<ets>kindeken</ets>, <ets>kinneken</ets>, a small barrel, orig., a
little child, fr. <ets>kind</ets> child; akin to G. <ets>kind</ets>, and
to E. <ets>kin</ets>.]</ety> <def>A small barrel; an old liquid measure
containing eighteen English beer gallons, or nearly twenty-two gallons,
United States measure.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>kinderkin</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kilerg</ent>⟦br⟧
